experience.description:
- Compile, organize and process incoming customer orders / documentation for distribution to related functions;
- Review orders for accuracy and request revisions when necessary;
- Analyze and verify contractual specifications pertaining to incoming orders;
- Authorize the order acceptance / rejection;
- Regularly produce or assist with production of order status reports;
- Organize conference Calls with sales team to discuss Pipeline;
- Update Sales Force according to Sales Team’s comments;
- Participation in weekly revenue recognition status call, proactive provision of order status updates.

- The distribution of work volume (maintenance of antenna constructions and base stations reports) between the employees of the Group (5 people);
- Checking the reports; 
- Figuring out antenna constructions’ defects at photo reports; 
- Sending the reports to customers, eliminating drawbacks;
- Communicating with employees who perform the maintenance regarding shortcomings of the performance;
- Creating excel stencils for reports;
- Calculation of payment for employees who work with piece-rate wages.

- Checking contractors payment documents for compliance with Russian law;
- Informing the contractors about mistakes in the documents;
- Checking if the work was really made by the contractors with the heads of the branches;
- Acceptance of works in huawei systems;
- Controlling if payments for the contractors are made in time; 
- Preparation and reconciliation of financial documents for the customer;
- Information support of the Chinese colleagues in the headquarter.

- Checking primary documents for compliance with Russian law (acts, bills, invoices, expense reports).
- Scanning and load the original documents in the Huawei system;
- Processing the documents in Huawei systems; 
- Negotiations with employees and members of remote accounting center in China (in English);
- Archiving documents;
- Creating contracts of employees’ liability.
